!! Introduction

Right-clicking any element with source position tracking enabled opens the DevTools context menu instead of the browser's default menu.

[img[screenshot-context-menu]]

!! Menu Header

The header row shows the source position (e.g., `L5 @ GettingStarted`) with three icon buttons:

|! Icon |! Action |! Description |
|! Pencil |Edit at position |Opens the tiddler in edit mode and auto-selects the corresponding source text range, scrolling the textarea to the selection |
|! Eye |Show source |Appends the source code entry to the [[Source Viewer]] panel |
|! X |Close |Closes the context menu |

!! Menu Items

Below the header, the menu offers these actions:

|! Item |! Description |
|! Copy tiddler title |Copies the source tiddler title to the clipboard |
|! Copy source position |Copies the full position info including context and caller chain |
|! Inspect variables |Opens the [[Variable Inspector]] showing all variables in scope at the clicked element |
|! Open //tiddlerTitle// |Navigates to the source tiddler in the story river |
|! Edit at L//range// |Opens the tiddler in edit mode and selects the source range (only visible when `ShowEditMenuItem` is enabled — see [[Configuration]]) |
|! Edit inline |Opens the [[Inline Editor]] popup (only visible when `ShowEditInline` is enabled — see [[Configuration]]) |
|! Open &larr; //callerTitle// |One entry per caller in the transclusion chain — navigates to that caller tiddler |

!! Keyboard Modifiers

| ! Action |! Effect |
| ''Right-click'' |Opens DevTools context menu |
| ''Ctrl+right-click'' |Passes through to native browser context menu |
| ''Ctrl+click'' |Directly navigates to the source tiddler (no menu) |

!! How It Works

The context menu replaces the browser's native `contextmenu` event when the clicked element (or any ancestor) has a `data-source-pos` attribute. It is rendered as a plain DOM overlay — no TiddlyWiki store writes, so it does not interfere with TW's refresh cycle or popup system.

